Description: Fragment of oval, tapering, handle from neck join to sharp turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-buff. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Name Aristanax. Same die is probably used in an example in Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0066.01.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (56)
